article.headline: (25) NORTH CAROLINA 89, UNC ASHEVILLE 47
article.story:
CHAPEL HILL, North Carolina (Ticker) -- Reyshawn Terry and 
North Carolina bounced back strong, much to the misery of UNC
Asheville.

Terry scored 14 points and freshman Danny Green added 15 as the
No. 25 Tar Heels rebounded from an embarrassing loss to thrash
the Bulldogs, 89-47.

Improving to 3-0 against its intrastate rival, North Carolina
(7-2) recovered from its first loss in eight all-time meetings
with Southern California, a 74-59 setback last Wednesday.

The team's second-leading scorer, Terry was a major culprit in
the tough loss, being held without a point on 0-of-4 shooting.

The junior forward bounced back in fine fashion Wednesday,
shooting 5-of-12 from the field and pulling down five rebounds.

After David Noel scored five points on a 13-0 run that broke a
4-4 score, Terry connected on his first basket with 13:22
remaining.  He added another over five minutes later to extend
the advantage to 33-9.

Overall, Terry scored 11 points in the first half as the Tar
Heels raced to a 53-20 lead at the break.  The squad cruised in
the second half en route to improving to 6-1 at the Smith
Center.

Green pulled down a season-high 11 rebounds and fellow freshman
Tyler Hansbrough added 14 points and eight steals for North
Carolina, which shot 45 percent (30-of-67) and finished with
five players in double figures.

Oliver Holmes scored 16 points for UNC Asheville (2-8), which
committed 29 turnovers.
